"Stolyarov M.V.","Cyclicity and some characteristics of mass reproduction of Calliptamus italicus l. in southern Russia",2000,"Russian Journal of Ecology","31","1",,"43","48",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-27844539926&partnerID=40&md5=e33ccb066983f8a6496201dcd408d4c1","All-Russian Research Institute of Plant Biological Protection, Russian Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Krasnodar, 350039, Russian Federation","Stolyarov, M.V., All-Russian Research Institute of Plant Biological Protection, Russian Academy of Agricultural Sciences, Krasnodar, 350039, Russian Federation","Analysis of the reproductive dynamics of Calliptamus italicus during the past 100 years confirmed the dependence of locust invasions on the 11 -year cycles of solar activity, which was previously known for other gregarious locusts. Over a considerable part of the species range, the onset of mass reproduction is promoted by a hot and droughty spring and summer. The scale of the outbreak is determined by local conditions in the foci of reproduction. The current global warming is characterized by an unstable, drastically varying climate with a trend toward aridity in many regions. If this trend persists for several decades, we may expect an increase in the periods of C. talictis mass reproduction and in the persistency and extent of damage inflicted by locusts on vast Palearctic areas.","Cyclicity; Drought. © 2000 maik ""nauka/interperiodica""; Locusts; Reproduction; Sun",,,,,,,"Ashworth, A.C., Changes in Insect Biodiversity in Response to Pleistocene Climate Change: Abstracts of Annual Meeting, Winnipeg, 1993 (1993) Proc. Entomol. Soc. Manit., 49, pp. 37-38; Avramenko, I.D., Italian Locust Is a Pest Detrimental to Pine Plantations (1958) Lesn. Khoz., (2), p. 92; Barabanova, V.A., Rhythms in the Development of the Codling Moth and the Role of Space Factors in Their Manifestation (1994) Zashchita Rastenii Ot Vreditelei, Boleznei i Sornoi Rastitel'nosti (Plant Protection from Pests